So based on what you already know

00:00:31.124 --> 00:00:33.074
about definite integrals,

00:00:33.074 --> 00:00:35.582
how would you actually
try to calculate this?

00:00:35.582 --> 00:00:38.159
Well one natural thing that you might say

00:00:38.159 --> 00:00:39.297
is well look,

00:00:39.297 --> 00:00:41.317
if I were to take the integral

00:00:41.317 --> 00:00:42.234
from a to b

00:00:43.430 --> 00:00:44.763
of f of x dx,

00:00:46.844 --> 00:00:49.514
that would give me the entire area

00:00:49.514 --> 00:00:50.514
below f of x

00:00:51.720 --> 00:00:53.833
and above the x-axis.

00:00:53.833 --> 00:00:56.132
And then if I were to subtract from that

00:00:56.132 --> 00:00:58.848
this area right over here,

00:00:58.848 --> 00:01:00.776
which is equal to

00:01:00.776 --> 00:01:03.585
that's the definite integral from a to b

00:01:03.585 --> 00:01:04.918
of g of x dx.

00:01:07.045 --> 00:01:09.530
Well then I would net out
with the original area

00:01:09.530 --> 00:01:10.830
that I cared about.

00:01:10.830 --> 00:01:13.709
I would net out with this
area right over here.

00:01:13.709 --> 00:01:15.869
And that indeed would be the case.

00:01:15.869 --> 00:01:17.842
And we know from our
integration properties

00:01:17.842 --> 00:01:19.421
that we can rewrite this as

00:01:19.421 --> 00:01:21.348
the integral from a to b

00:01:21.348 --> 00:01:24.715
of, let me put some parentheses here,

00:01:24.715 --> 00:01:25.548
of f of x

00:01:27.409 --> 00:01:28.492
minus g of x,

00:01:29.986 --> 00:01:30.986
minus g of x

00:01:34.189 --> 00:01:35.559
dx.

00:01:35.559 --> 00:01:37.254
And now I'll make a claim to you,

00:01:37.254 --> 00:01:39.228
and we'll build a little
bit more intuition for this

00:01:39.228 --> 00:01:40.946
as we go through this video,

00:01:40.946 --> 00:01:43.245
but over an integral from a to b

00:01:43.245 --> 00:01:45.497
where f of x is greater than g of x,

00:01:45.497 --> 00:01:46.821
like this interval right over here,

00:01:46.821 --> 00:01:49.398
this is always going to be the case,

00:01:49.398 --> 00:01:51.395
that the area between the curves

00:01:51.395 --> 00:01:53.415
